    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "54600085_95ceb3e3",
        "filename": "go/task_driver/examples/basic/basic.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 64,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-11T12:00:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Arguments to deferred funcs get evaluated in the defer statement, not when the func is called.  In the case the function-scoped step, we have to pass a pointer or the error passed to Done will always be nil.  That allows us to do this:\n\nfunc(s *Step) (err error) {\n    s \u003d s.Step().Start()\n    defer s.Done(\u0026err)\n\n    ...\n}\n\ninstead of this:\n\nfunc(s *Step) (err error) {\n    s \u003d s.Step().Start()\n    defer func() {\n        s.Done(err)\n    }()\n\n    ...\n}",
      "parentUuid": "ad59b604_3b618cbd",
      "revId": "320e47702b2df9cd17d33e31ca179ad922c8d991",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "b4bfb0a2_7f8b6edd",
        "filename": "go/task_driver/examples/basic/basic.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-10T20:03:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "The .Start()\nerr :\u003d ....\n.Done(err)\n\nis going to get tedious, and is much easier to understand in the Do format:\n\ns.Step().Infra().Env(env).Name(\"named infra step with env\").Do(func (s *Step) error {\n  return nil\n})\n\nI think this is easier to read.",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 69,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "320e47702b2df9cd17d33e31ca179ad922c8d991",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "4a8e281b_fe22c7b6",
        "filename": "go/task_driver/examples/basic/basic.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 72,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-11T12:00:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Agreed.  Do() and the function-scoped step shown below are the recommended usages.  I was trying to introduce the basic building blocks of Steps first, but what I should\u0027ve done was introduce the most basic *usage* first. I changed these first couple of examples to use Do() and added a later section recommending against this usage pattern (ie. storing a new step as a local variable and calling Done() outside of a defer).",
      "parentUuid": "b4bfb0a2_7f8b6edd",
      "range": {
        "startLine": 70,
        "startChar": 69,
        "endLine": 72,
        "endChar": 17
      },
      "revId": "320e47702b2df9cd17d33e31ca179ad922c8d991",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
