      "writtenOn": "2018-10-11T12:00:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I think the function-scoped usage is nicer than Do() for anything but very small chunks of work.  Do() will result in multiple levels of indent and IMO will be harder to read.  FTR Do() is pretty much what I had written in my first patch set of the original experimentation CL.  Once I started getting into writing \"real\" sets of steps with non-trivial amounts of work, it was much harder to read.",
