        "id": 5205
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-10T20:03:53Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "Why not use the same functionality that fluentd uses and differentiate between regular logs and structured logs, i.e. structured logs are simply single log lines that can be parsed as valid JSON. If we do that then HandleMessage goes away, as those are just become structured logs.",
      "revId": "320e47702b2df9cd17d33e31ca179ad922c8d991",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
    {
      "key": {
        "uuid": "e67edbf1_203be873",
        "filename": "go/task_driver/receiver.go",
        "patchSetId": 1
      },
      "lineNbr": 20,
      "author": {
        "id": 5015
      },
      "writtenOn": "2018-10-11T12:00:20Z",
      "side": 1,
      "message": "I like having these be separate calls because it places the burden of differentiating between types of messages on the emitter rather than the receiver.  Otherwise, for example, the ReportReceiver would need to determine whether the message is valid JSON (including potentially buffering to ensure that it has received the entire string of bytes which makes up the message) in order to decide whether it\u0027s dealing with step metadata or logs, which are treated differently.  Another example is the PubSubReceiver (coming in a subsequent CL) which just drops all logs on the floor but sends pubsub messages for step metadata.",
      "parentUuid": "db2356ad_b5654e73",
      "revId": "320e47702b2df9cd17d33e31ca179ad922c8d991",
      "serverId": "5086850b-e599-37d2-8ec8-ff16aeccbf02",
      "unresolved": true
    },
